README.md
     5‚Üí# ‚åòK [![cmdk minzip package size](https://img.shields.io/bundlephobia/minzip/cmdk)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/cmdk?activeTab=code) [![cmdk package version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/cmdk.svg?colorB=green)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/cmdk)
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí‚åòK is a command menu React component that can also be used as an accessible combobox. You render items, it filters and sorts them automatically. ‚åòK supports a fully composable API <sup><sup>[How?](/ARCHITECTURE.md)</sup></sup>, so you can wrap items in other components or even as static JSX.
     9‚Üí## Install
    10‚Üí
    11‚Üí```bash
    12‚Üípnpm install cmdk
    13‚Üí```
    15‚Üí## Use
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí```tsx
    18‚Üíimport { Command } from 'cmdk'
    82‚Üí## Parts and styling
    83‚Üí
    84‚ÜíAll parts forward props, including `ref`, to an appropriate element. Each part has a specific data-attribute (starting with `cmdk-`) that can be used for styling.
    86‚Üí### Command `[cmdk-root]`
    87‚Üí
    88‚ÜíRender this to show the command menu inline, or use [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) to render in a elevated context. Can be controlled with the `value` and `onValueChange` props.
   153‚Üí### Dialog `[cmdk-dialog]` `[cmdk-overlay]`
   154‚Üí
   155‚ÜíProps are forwarded to [Command](#command-cmdk-root). Composes Radix UI's Dialog component. The overlay is always rendered. See the [Radix Documentation](https://www.radix-ui.com/docs/primitives/components/dialog) for more information. Can be controlled with the `open` and `onOpenChange` props.
   180‚Üí### Input `[cmdk-input]`
   181‚Üí
   182‚ÜíAll props are forwarded to the underlying `input` element. Can be controlled with the `value` and `onValueChange` props.
   190‚Üí### List `[cmdk-list]`
   191‚Üí
   192‚ÜíContains items and groups. Animate height using the `--cmdk-list-height` CSS variable.
   212‚Üí### Item `[cmdk-item]` `[data-disabled?]` `[data-selected?]`
   213‚Üí
   214‚ÜíItem that becomes active on pointer enter. You should provide a unique `value` for each item, but it will be automatically inferred from the `.textContent`.
   242‚Üí### Group `[cmdk-group]` `[hidden?]`
   243‚Üí
   244‚ÜíGroups items together with the given `heading` (`[cmdk-group-heading]`).
   256‚Üí### Separator `[cmdk-separator]`
   257‚Üí
   258‚ÜíVisible when the search query is empty or `alwaysRender` is true, hidden otherwise.
   260‚Üí### Empty `[cmdk-empty]`
   261‚Üí
   262‚ÜíAutomatically renders when there are no results for the search query.
   264‚Üí### Loading `[cmdk-loading]`
   265‚Üí
   266‚ÜíYou should conditionally render this with `progress` while loading asynchronous items.
   274‚Üí### `useCommandState(state => state.selectedField)`
   275‚Üí
   276‚ÜíHook that composes [`useSyncExternalStore`](https://reactjs.org/docs/hooks-reference.html#usesyncexternalstore). Pass a function that returns a slice of the command menu state to re-render when that slice changes. This hook is provided for advanced use cases and should not be commonly used.
   285‚Üí## Examples
   286‚Üí
   287‚ÜíCode snippets for common use cases.
   289‚Üí### Nested items
   290‚Üí
   291‚ÜíOften selecting one item should navigate deeper, with a more refined set of items. For example selecting "Change theme‚Ä¶" should show new items "Dark theme" and "Light theme". We call these sets of items "pages", and they can be implemented with simple state:
   338‚Üí### Show sub-items when searching
   339‚Üí
   340‚ÜíIf your items have nested sub-items that you only want to reveal when searching, render based on the search state:
   361‚Üí### Asynchronous results
   362‚Üí
   363‚ÜíRender the items as they become available. Filtering and sorting will happen automatically.
   397‚Üí### Use inside Popover
   398‚Üí
   399‚ÜíWe recommend using the [Radix UI popover](https://www.radix-ui.com/docs/primitives/components/popover) component. ‚åòK relies on the Radix UI Dialog component, so this will reduce your bundle size a bit due to shared dependencies.
   426‚Üí### Drop in stylesheets
   427‚Üí
   428‚ÜíYou can find global stylesheets to drop in as a starting point for styling. See [website/styles/cmdk](website/styles/cmdk) for examples.
   430‚Üí## FAQ
   431‚Üí
   432‚Üí**Accessible?** Yes. Labeling, aria attributes, and DOM ordering tested with Voice Over and Chrome DevTools. [Dialog](#dialog-cmdk-dialog-cmdk-overlay) composes an accessible Dialog implementation.
   456‚Üí## History
   457‚Üí
   458‚ÜíWritten in 2019 by Paco ([@pacocoursey](https://twitter.com/pacocoursey)) to see if a composable combobox API was possible. Used for the Vercel command menu and autocomplete by Rauno ([@raunofreiberg](https://twitter.com/raunofreiberg)) in 2020. Re-written independently in 2022 with a simpler and more performant approach. Ideas and help from Shu ([@shuding\_](https://twitter.com/shuding_)).
   462‚Üí## Testing
   463‚Üí
